Malky Mackay was sacked by Wigan Athletic on Monday after a 2-0 defeat by Derby . 
  Sportsmail revealed in August he was being investigated over 'sexist, racism and homophobic' texts  . 
  Dave Whelan appointed Mackay as manager of Wigan in November 2014 but has arguably harmed the club . 
  Wigan face relegation from the Championship this season . 
  Mackay has failed to win a home game in his six months in charge . 
 